1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Bb4 5. e5 h6 6. Bd2 Bxc3 7. bxc3 Ne4 8. Qg4
g6 {An important alternative to 8...Kf8. This move has the disadvantage of the
weak f6 square.} 9. Bd3 Nxd2 10. Kxd2 c5 11. Nf3 Nc6 12. Qf4 $1 {This move is
very important - pointing to the f6 square.} (12. h4 {Is a typical Maccutcheon
move, but 12. Qf4 is more accurate in this particular position.}) 12... cxd4
13. cxd4 Qa5+ 14. c3 b6 {With the idea of exchanging the bishops. Now White
has a very deep plan to gain the advantage.} 15. Qf6 Rg8 16. a4 $1 {This is
the idea: White is going to allow the exchange but only under favourable
circumstances - taking advantage of the bad position of Black's queen.} Ba6 17.
Bb5 $1 Bxb5 18. axb5 Qxb5 19. Rhb1 Qc4 20. Rxb6 $1 Rc8 $4 {This line is
already bad for Black, but after this move White wins in a very simple way...}
(20... Nd8 21. Ne1 $1 Qc7 22. Rba6 Nc6 23. Nd3 $1 {This strong manoeuvre gives
White a clear advantage; Black can`t coordinate his pieces.}) 21. Rb7 a5 (21...
Rf8 22. Raxa7 {And it's all over...}) 22. Qxf7+ 1-0

